    <text id="B1070T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson asks permission to employ a clerk during a particularly busy period in
                    his office.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="section" id="wrapper">
                <p>Bureau R.F. &amp; A.L.<lb/><abbr expan="Headquarters">Head Qrs.</abbr> 9th
                        <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr><lb/>Winchester, Va. June 25/67<lb/>Respectfully
                    forwarded to <abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig. Gen.</abbr>
                    <hi rend="underline">O. Brown</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst. Comr.</abbr> State of Va <hi
                        rend="underline">append</hi> - Mr <hi rend="underline">Jackson</hi> has
                    lately from some cause been unable to perform the duties required, with his
                    usual promptitude.<lb/>[signed] John A. McDonnell, <abbr
                        expan="Captain and Sub Assistant Commissioner">Capt. &amp;
                S.A.C.</abbr></p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Office 4th Division, 9th
                    Sub-District, Virginia.
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr> John A.
                            McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub Asst
                        Comr</abbr><lb/>Winchester</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-06-23">June 23 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Captain</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I respectfully ask permission to engage a clerk at this office until completion
                    of Registration <add hand="h1" place="inline">and Elections</add> in Augusta
                    County. The business of 4th <abbr expan="Division">Div.</abbr> is very large and
                    the Freedmen widely scattered and together with the duties of Registering
                    officers I find I am not able single handed to keep up effectively with
                        <unclear>outdoor</unclear> and office work</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="Your obedient servant">Yr. obt. servt</abbr>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P. Jackson</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="underline">Agent</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
